A congressman was tricked into retweeting photos of Nazis and war criminals.

Darrell Issa, a Californian Republican, started retweeting pictures of US military veterans in a publicity stunt on Twitter that has courted significant traffic for his account in the past.

But it seems he and his media team weren't paying astute attention to the images being sent to them.

